e\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dalard\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"sexually transmitted diseases\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"fliers\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"posters\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangers\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"consent\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The European Union's health agency warned on March 7 about a \\\"troubling\\\" surge in sexually transmitted infections (STIs) across the continent over the previous year.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1619, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999984147507, \"rank\": 1.1159321638880653e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"troubling\\\" surge\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"sexually transmitted infections\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"STIs\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"the continent\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous year\", \"from\": 1753, \"to\": 1770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, gonorrhoea cases in the EU rose by 48 per cent, syphilis was up 34 and chlamydia 16 per cent, according to the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC).\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1806, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999966809708041, \"rank\": 3.3175879859951076e-06, \"text\": \"EU\